text.paragraph:

   Fluoroquinolones, including ciprofloxacin are associated with an increased risk of tendonitis and tendon rupture in all ages. This risk is further increased in older patients usually over 60 years of age, in patients taking corticosteroid drugs, and in patients with kidney, heart or lung transplants (See
 

      WARNINGS

).


   Fluoroquinolones, inlcuding ciprofloxacin, may exacerbate muscle weakness in persons with myasthenia gravis.  Avoid ciprofloxacin in patients with known history of myasthenia gravis (See
 

      WARNINGS

).
